
[1]orgues

   OR'GUES, n.

   1. In the military art, long thick pieces of timber, pointed and shod
   with iron and hung over a gateway, to be let down in case of attack.

   2. A machine composed of several musket barrels united, by means of
   which several explosions are made at once to defend breaches.
